channel.title: Whats this mean and how do i fix it?
channel.description:
C:\Documents and Settings\Compaq_Owner\Desktop>java -Xmx512m -jar SilabClient.j ar 0 0 highmem members 0 'java' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file. C:\Documents and Settings\Compaq_Owner\Desktop>pause Press any key to continue . . .
How can i fix this?

item.title: Whats this mean and how do i fix it?
item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

Look in your Program Filesfolder (%PROGRAMFILES%) for something that says “Java”. Then look in there for something that says (jdk_***) where the *** represents dots and numbers. Just copy the whole thing (including the jdk_ part) into where it says your classpath.
